text: Dewayne Michael Carey, 59, an inmate on San Quentin’s Death Row, died in an outside hospital Saturday from what authorities say appeared to be complications related to COVID-19. https://t.co/FVaUQs5ZqK

name: sfchronicle
text:
A South Bay school district employee who allegedly coughed on an infant in a San Jose Yogurtland shop no longer works for the district, the superintendent said.

https://t.co/Zt8P6rjBhP

name: sfchronicle
sfchronicle
text:
Everything about this July 4 was a little different

Most everything was closed, canceled, or hard to get at if open. Sitting on the beach or a park lawn was possible for the masked and the socially distant. Parking nearby, in most cases, wasn’t. 

https://t.co/jUhQwJk4A4 https://t.co/tQLPX8sFYs

name: sfchronicle
text:
Rents in the Bay Area plummeted last month. See some of the biggest drops, by city:
▪️Cupertino: -15.7% to $2,680
▪️Mountain View: -15.1% to $2,930
▪️San Francisco: -11.8% to $3,280

*Based on median rents for 1-bedrooms listed in June
Read more: https://t.co/584MRKHsCE

name: sfchronicle
text:
The @Athletics held their first workout since baseball's shutdown. Pitchers and catchers worked in staggered groups, coaches maintained their distance, masks were de rigueur. 

“Everything is going to be different,” manager Bob Melvin said. https://t.co/SeyHYqlM5e

name: sfchronicle
text:
At the Giants' full-speed batting practice, Buster Posey was particularly impressed by pitcher Logan Webb, the 23-year-old who debuted last season and was vying for the fifth spot in the rotation when the shutdown began.

https://t.co/UyBEIAGcsO

name: sfchronicle
text:
Giants management already promised that it won’t be a traditional five-man rotation in which the starters throw a bunch of innings. Openers could be used far more often, with “bulk” pitchers to follow, or a couple of guys tossing three innings apiece.

https://t.co/7sGuSAbUt0

name: sfchronicle
text: Firefighters contained a a grass fire at San Francisco's McLaren park that burned through four acres of brush and hillside. https://t.co/N1h8wfp8xL

name: sfchronicle
text: BREAKING: Grass fires flare up across San Francisco — in McLaren Park, Hunters Point and North Beach. At least one of them is linked to illegal fireworks.  https://t.co/xNZI0jOokM
